      mid: "~$200-300 loose / ~$500-4,000 finished. The Swiss-Japanese mainstream: ETA 2824-2 and its drop-in clones Sellita SW200-1 and Seagull ST2130, the slimmer ETA 2892-A2, the higher-end Miyota 9015, and Seiko's 4R/6R/Spring Drive-adjacent calibers. Brands here include Hamilton, Tissot, Longines, Oris, Tudor (in-house MT calibers), and Sinn. Often chronometer-grade or close to it.",
